  "prompt": "How do you play the game Snaps?",
  "response": "Snaps is a fun word game that involves guessing a secret word based on clues given by a host. Here\u2019s a quick guide on how to play the game:\n\n### Objective:\nThe goal is to guess the secret word chosen by the host using the clues provided.\n\n### Players:\n- Minimum of 2 players; can be played with larger groups.\n\n### Setup:\n1. **Choose a Host**: One player is chosen to be the host, who will think of a secret word.\n2. **Select a Secret Word**: The host thinks of a word (it can be anything, but preferably a common noun).\n\n### Gameplay:\n1. **Provide Clues**: The host gives clues to the players to help them guess the secret word. However, the host must incorporate a specific rhythm or pattern, often using the word \"snaps.\"\n  \n2. **Snapping**: \n   - When the host gives a clue, they may snap their fingers to signal the clues. \n   - For example, if the secret word starts with \"C,\" the host might say \"C,\" followed by snapping fingers to indicate something about the letter/word.\n\n3. **Guessing**: \n   - Players take turns guessing the secret word based on the clues provided. If someone guesses correctly, they win and can either take over as the host or continue playing.\n   - If players guess incorrectly, the host can provide more hints or clues, possibly changing the rhythm or adding complexity.\n\n### Tips:\n- The game works best with clever associations and lateral thinking. The clues should be given in a way that leads players in the right direction without being too obvious.\n- Players can make it a timed challenge or keep it casual, depending on the group's preference.\n\n### End of Game:\n- The game can continue until players lose interest, or until a pre-decided number of rounds/cycles is completed.\n\nHave fun playing Snaps! Adjust the rules as needed to fit your group's preferences.",
